description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pelvic Health Physiotherapist B6 or 7&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Be outstanding-join an outstanding team!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do you strive to develop and support your team whilst providing expert patient centered care to empower patients to improve their quality of life? If so we have the job for you. The pelvic health physiotherapy team are based in the Brownsword Therapies Centre which opened in 2019 including a hydrotherapy suite, gym, integrated outpatient therapies and technology facilities to support virtual services.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for an experienced pelvic health physiotherapist who is dedicated to patient care, development of the team and service progression. There are both band 6 and 7 opportunities available dependent upon experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 pelvic health physiotherapists will particpate in weekend working to support inpatient services.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Informal visits are welcomed and for further information please contact alexandra.marris@nhs.net or claireyoung2@nhs.net &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
